🇮🇳 India General Election Results Analysis - 2024 (Power BI)
📊 Project Overview

This project presents an interactive Power BI dashboard analyzing the India General Election Results 2024.
The goal is to transform raw election data into meaningful insights at national, state, and constituency levels.

🎯 Objectives
Analyze overall election performance of major alliances (NDA, I.N.D.I.A., Others)
Understand state-wise political dominance
Provide constituency-level insights including winners and vote share
Build an interactive and user-friendly dashboard for data exploration
📌 Key Features
🔹 Overview Analysis
Total Seats: 543
NDA: 292 (54%)
I.N.D.I.A.: 234 (43%)
Others: 17 (3%)
Party-wise performance visualization
🔹 State Demographics Analysis
Map visualization showing state-wise dominance
Drill-down capability for deeper insights
Comparison of NDA vs I.N.D.I.A. seats
🔹 Constituency Analysis
Winning Candidate
Runner-Up and 2nd Runner-Up
Total Votes & Vote Share
Detailed candidate-level insights
🔹 State Analysis
State-wise filtering (e.g., Chandigarh)
Party-wise results
Seat distribution using donut chart
🧠 Key Insights
NDA secured majority with 292 seats (54%)
I.N.D.I.A. alliance showed strong competition with 234 seats
Significant variation in political dominance across states
Some states are heavily dominated by a single alliance
🛠 Tools & Technologies
Power BI
DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)
Data Modeling
Excel
⚙️ Data Modeling
Multiple tables used:
constituencywise_results
constituencywise_details
partywise_results
states
Relationships created using:
Party ID
Constituency ID
State
🔢 Key DAX Calculations
✅ Winner Logic

Used MAX and CALCULATE to identify candidates with highest votes.

✅ Runner-Up & 2nd Runner-Up

Used advanced DAX:

MAX
FILTER
MAXX

This logic dynamically calculates:

Winner
Runner-Up
Second Runner-Up
✅ Alliance Mapping

Used IF conditions and LOOKUPVALUE to classify parties into:

NDA
I.N.D.I.A.
Others
✅ Seat Share %

Used DIVIDE() function for safe calculations:

NDA %
I.N.D.I.A. %
Others %

